\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I don't know about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 When you were a child how did you get on with your brothers and your sisters and was there anyone you were specially close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well we used fight a bit you know. We - one of this - that's nine you see, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Was there anyone you felt especially close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well I were always fond of me parents. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You always felt close to them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Yes. Always fond of me parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 As a child who did you play with - your brothers and sisters or neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well we used to mix it up a bit you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Like I tell you, used to play ball and cricket and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 In the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No, 
on a field - there used to be a spare ground you see, we used to play on this spare ground. It's where - it's where the - they used to tip all their - all their ashes and that for council do you see, but we used to burn all paper - used to be burned - all
 paper and all tins and that picked out and then they used to level ground out and it made like a bit of a play ground you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you ever play in the house - were you allowed to come in the house to play - you and your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 It just depends what we were playing at. If it were a rough game we were - soon had it. Were thrown out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played or did you get into trouble if you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Dirty? Sometimes you couldn't tell whether we were white - whether we were white or black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What happened - did you get into trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well me dad says, you got in it you'll have get out of it. He says, and go and wash your face it's dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 could you play with anyone you pleased or did they stop you playing with certain children? Did they ever choose your friends for you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I don't know they did. You had to choose them yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You never stopped you playing with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 They never stopped you for playing with anybody. Only - only when - when som
eone had measles. Then they stopped us. Used to say, keep away from them, they've got measles - that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you belong to any youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you keep any pets or collect anything or do any gardening? Did your mum and dad grow their own vegetables or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 She used to buy all her vegetables. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you do any gardening or have pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No, I said it's too much work. When I were younger I said it's too much work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Didn't you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No more than bowling - watching 'em bowl and - playing - playing dominoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You didn't take part in sport yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No, only watching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you ever go to theatres or concerts when you were a child - or cinemas while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh, we used go pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 When?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Saturday afternoons. There were always a children's do at Saturday afternoon. I - I don't know whether you used to pay threepence or not for go in. And - there - they used to be silent pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did anyone outside the home help your mother if she was ill - relations or friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - if she wasn't so well they'd come in and give a bit of a lift you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 This was relations or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Friends. Friends. Neighbours. Neighbours close to, they come in and give a bit of a lift you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 They used to come in and help your mum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 That's - that - that's just the way it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 They'd help with the wash and help with the cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 They make everything straigh
t for you and do a little bit of washing, but no bedding. No. They wouldn't do any bedding because it were heavy and - and they wanted some heavy squeezers for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Not close to, no. Me dad - me dad wouldn't have 'em. He said, you're better off away from your relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 He said they caused bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How would they cause bother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Be - they come - they come with all their ups and downs and - it's putting a burden on you and he says you'
ve enough with your own troubles without taking anybody else\rquote s on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did your parents have a lot of friends and did they share their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 We used to share with them. They had friends. That used to come visiting but - they never made a practice
 of - all going regular to such a place and such a place you see. They just used to meet them casually you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did your mother have her own friends - friends that were just your mother's or did your father have his own friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - friends when he were going to these bird singing matches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 He'd make friends there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Aye, he used to have more friends then because they all wanted to know who'd won you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 But your mother didn't have a lot of friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 She pi
cked up when she went to church you know. Used to have friends from church and if she wasn't so well she - they'd come and visit you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What about neighbours, did they come in visiting or did they just come in when they wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 They just - th
ey didn't make a practice of - what you may - always being in. That's - that's like watching you - for every meal. They didn't make a practice of that. But they did come in if there were anything wrong - if they wasn't so well and helping out. Aye. They d
idn't make a practice of - of neighbouring as you may call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
People often say - in those days when you were with your friends - when your parents were with their friends they made their own amusements. How did your parents amuse themselves when they 
were with their friends, do you remember? Did they play games or did they make music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Well they used to - have all - they used to have these concerts at schools. And they used to be - playing in parks - band playing in parks which there is now. And t
here used to be a concertina band at Westhoughton. All playing these 'ere concertinas you know. I don't know how that come for be broke up but - it were - it were fetched up I think at Westhoughton. And you could go in t' park and listen these bands you k
now and have a look all round and - walk all round. That's way they used to pass their time away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Suppose the friends came inside the house how would they spend the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well it just depends whether they were dry or not. If they're dry they have a drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 They wouldn't sing or play games or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
No, no. No, they wouldn't sing or play - just - just come chatting that's all and - telling all their - so and so and so and so and - that's all you'd get out of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You were telling me anybody born in Westhoughton had to be called cowards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Anybody as was born in Westhoughton they call 'em cowards and that used to be the coat of arms and in some fancy shops you could buy ornaments with the gate on with the cows head through. And - oh I - did I mention that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You used to have wakes there - what were wakes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Always at the last Saturday in August it used to be called Westhoughton Wakes and them used to be people coming from far and near and they used to visit the pu
blic houses just to see the Cowhead dressed up. After that they'd go and buy pasties out at shop. Made of - made of pork - pasties made of pork. And if they were having a party they used to order a big one - anything from five shilling to a pound. And whe
n
 they were finishing up they used to go to a certain house where this party was being held and they used to drink bottles of beer and eat these pasties. That used carry on 'til about half past twelve. Then they used to find their way home. That - that was
 the finishing point of the wakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Tell me about the people at Westhoughton, were some people considered ladies and some gentlemen - do you remember different classes of people in Westhoughton and can you describe them to me - before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well -
 all as I - all as I can remember is the Westhoughton gala. That's another - event. The - I didn't - I don't know what date but there used to be jazz bands and fancy dresses and they used to parade through Westhoughton right round the borough. Then they'd
 go on a field. And they'd distribute who'd won such prizes do you see. And - also there'd be dancing on that field. 'Til about nine o'clock, 'til it went something like dusk. Then they had to clear off. That was the fete of the gala.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 In those days di
d you think of some people belonging to one social group and some people belonging to another? Do you remember different levels, perhaps some were rough and some were respectable. Do you remember different types of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh yes, there - there was s
ome like that you know. But - there - there were some you know used to wear them knickerbockers. Pants you know as - were - used to go to at the bottom. They called 'em knickerbockers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Were these the posh people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - there was - in p
osh - posh in a way. In their own way but - you'd think it more like a navvy or something like that with his trousers tied up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you know any navvies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - all navies then you know, they used to tie their pants when they were going digging. 
For get ground out and work with musky and sludgy you know but now - they put them leg boots on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Do you ever remember anybody being referred to as a real gentleman or a real lady when you were a child and why do you think people called them that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - gentlemen is - is - is the way how he is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Can you describe it - what you mean by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 He can be gentle - to some people but not to others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What about a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well a real - a real lady is one as 'll mind her own business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 That's what you think do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Yes. That's a real lady. As 'll mind her own business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What class do you think you belonged to as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - it's always - it's the working class. I should belong to the working class. Because I've always had work for me living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 And you think all workers belong to this class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Were some people thought of as very rough and others as very respectable and can you describe the difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh there were plenty of people as were 
rough you know, rough and ready. They just tie a scarf you know into a knot and - bit of it hanging at back - they didn't care how they were as long as they were going to this - certain - engagement do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you ever remember anyone being called Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Were you ever told to touch your cap to anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1036\langfe1033\langnp1036\insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1036\langfe1033\langnp1036\insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Only t' parson. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Who was considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 It was a very strange thing. It was a very strange thing as happened with a parson and it was the parson at S
t James's church, Daisy Hill. Every Sunday morning there used be an old lady called Mrs Woods and her used to go t' public house wit' jug every Sunday morning. So - parson met her one Sunday. He says, Mrs Woods, what's the reason you go t' public house ev
ery Sunday dinner time wit' jug? Well her says, if I must tell you, her says, when I was a young child her says, I our chimney got on fire and her says, I got a spark down me throat and her says, every now and then it wants slacking out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Slacking out means washing out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You were telling me about the different streets and the different houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well there was - there were some as were posh you know and the - they used to think you were dirt at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Why because - they thought they were higher than you you know. Because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What type of people would these be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Well they were getting a good wage do you see, they were - like - a manager or a - or a boss or something like that - over a gang of people to you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 And they thought they were somebody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
They used think they were posh and they had the posh houses you know. Then you go into another street and you'd see children playing on t' front and you'd go in t' house flag floor and sand on t' floor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 This would be a poor house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Was there a big difference between craftsmen and labourers do you think when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - craftsmen, you know, used to set the job out and - it were left to you then. And - if you - if you didn't d
o it right - they'd come you know and they'd some awful words to you and you'd have to do it over again, you see. That's the craftsman\rquote 
s part. But - as far as you can get with craftsmen is - them as is over you. Them as is over you and there's somebody ove
r them. They're too much complicated do you see. That's where the difference lies. And with that complication it makes the working men as they don't take the same interest in their work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You think there was a difference in the interest of the workers do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You didn't think the working man took the same interest as the craftsmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
No. No. That's - that's through somebody being over him and interfering with him the craftsman put his orders and the working man - not like that you se
e. And that - that's made it bad on the job do you see. And it's made 'em - as they've had - had to come back again in a very short time to renew that job. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you think there was a difference of interest amongst the workers though? Between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 There - there was a division between them. And there was bother between them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Why - what kind of bother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well it - it was concerning wages you see. When - when you were on a certain job and it were a dirty jo
b you used to get a bit extra money for it you see. Well - some of these gaffers you know would try to rule that out as it wasn't dirty. That was putting you down and you were losing - wage. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you remember in Westhoughton who were the most impo
rtant people - do you remember anybody being thought of as very important when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 The election was the most important part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you remember any one person being thought of as important or any people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 They were - Roy Davis were important, he got in as Labour candidate. He was important there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Can you tell me who you thought the shopkeepers mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well they mixed with anybody as was spending plenty of money with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What about the teachers, who do you think they mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Teachers were very often round parsons. Ah - they used to make to parson. The teachers - when - especially when there was anything on at school or church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Who do you think the bosses mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well they were always - on the company's side. They were never on your side. And anything - anything they could rob you of they would do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you think so in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Yes. Yes. Well they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You mean your wages or in what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You'd have - you'd be set out 
to do a certain job do you see. Well - you'd have a price for doing that sort o' - o' work do you see. Well - the boss used come round. He'd say, you've not done it proper. Why, what's wrong? He says, you've not lifted that flag up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 And this way he'd try and knock your wages down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
He says, you'll not be paid full money, he says, unless you take that flag up, he says, there's a lot of dirt in there as wants cleaning out so's it'll leave a clear passage for - drains, you see. It was like access pool. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Which job was this you were working on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
That - that's the - the se here rate - these here roadmen as I'm speaking of now. It's roadmen where they're putting drains in do you see. And - they have what they call - a built cess pool. Well 
that's to catch all the dirt do you see. Well they used give 'em extra money for clearing that out. But - gaffer come round - he looked round and he says, you've not had flag up have you? Well he didn't say. But gaffer takes flag up, he says, you'll not g
et your money 'til you've cleaned that sump hole out So he had to clean it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Can you remember as a child ever being taught to treat some people different to another type? Do you remember being taught to touch your cap t anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I don't know - 
I don't know as I were because - only when we were - when we were going t' school you know, we used to get hold hands and - run off with one another you know, pulling one another. Sometimes a someone would go on t' floor and - we had turn back then and pi
ck 'em up do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Which kind of people do you think went to church and which kind went to chapel? Did you notice a difference between church and chapel people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 The only difference as they're all fighting to get to one place. That's all I can say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You didn't notice any difference at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
There's no - I don't see there any difference whether it was church, chapel or the Roman Catholics. They're all fighting to get to one place. And I don't see there - there were any difference only a
 slight difference in the services, that's all. In their methods and the services.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to one social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well she always had work for her living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You think she thought of herself as working class do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 As a working woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
When you were a boy do you think it was possible to move up in the world and how do you think you managed it - could you move up in the world at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well I - I - never - I never got in any higher standard than fourth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I mean when you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
No. I don't think - I don't think that was - I don't think that was so. No. The - the people as got the best jobs - got them through favouritism, that's what I think. The best jobs, they got them throug
h favouritsm. There was all - there was always favouritism showed so what you're working and to what trade you're in there were always favouritism and there's that yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 When you were a boy do you ever remember seeing a policeman around Westhoughton and do you remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457  you thought of him as a boy and did your mother ever say if you do anything wrong I'll tell a policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh her never said that. Mother -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you remember the police though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 We used to run out way when we saw policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Were you frightened of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 We were frightened of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Because he used to batter us wi' his cape do you see. He used to give us a bat wi' his cape you know if we were playing where we shouldn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well he - he had to treat them wi' a little bit o' - civility you know, because - he were - he - he was a government servant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 But he didn't treat the children like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No. He used to bat us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Was the house you lived in rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Yes. Yes, it was rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you ever see your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh I was see - well we didn't see landlord but we saw collector who used come round collecting and that was me. I used collect rents.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How did this come about - was this when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Well I - when we lived at Daisy Hill there were houses in Lee Road and there were houses in Mabel Street and me mother used to - set them when they come empty to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 She used to let them did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Yes, she used to let
 them. And I used to collect rents. And I had to take it to a office in Maudsley Street at Bolton. And - and the fellows name then was Shipperbotham. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How old would you be when you were doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well it was - it was for a time do you see, it was for a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 While you were at school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I - I - I only did it at weekend. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Was it while you were at school though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No, it was while I was working that I did this - I should have left school then. Used to go round for 
this - for't rents you know. Collect these 'ere rents. But one time when I went round - I goes down Mabel Street and there's a little lad playing soon as ever he sees me he sets off running you know. He says, mammy, rent man's coming. So when I got to doo
r
, door were locked. Door were locked. I didn't get me rent so I had to mark a cross agen that. When I went to - t' pay in at Maudsley Street and saw this, oh, he said, they've not paid for a considerable time. I says, no. Oh, he says, we must have them ou
t.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did they put them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 So - he gave them notice. They didn't move. He takes front door off and he takes back door off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 While they were still in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 While they was in t'house. They fetched lav}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 rty door to front door. They put 
that up front and they fetched a room door from upstairs for back - took it off and put it at back. That didn't stop them - making them go. So he took windows out. They went and got shawls and - cloth. Covered windows up like that there. So I goes one wee
k, I says, they're still in. He says, I know they are, he says, but we - he says, we will get 'em out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Were they very poor and they couldn't afford then rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No - it were because they thought more about drink than paying their road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you get a lot of people like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Well - when I saw - when I went to - Maudsley Street I told him that they're still in he says, yes, he says, I know they're in he says, but, he says, we'll get them out. We'll have them out. I says, why, what're you go
ing to do? He says, I'm going tell a fellow go and put a slate inside of chimney pot. So one fellow went at night time and put a slate - put a slate inside the chimney pot. And they went then. They'd no - they'd no furniture. He'd sent bums you know -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 They're the bailiffs aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Bailiffs. He'd sent them and cleaned their furniture out. Yes. That was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What were they living on then - how did they sleep and eat?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh they couldn't take the beds. Oh they couldn't take the beds but th
ey could take anything else then. Anything only the beds, they couldn't take the beds. And - the - they used to have orange box for dine off. Empty orange box, long orange box about this length you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What would they sit on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - anything they could get. They'd get a bucket and put a piece of wood across and sit on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 But the father was working - it wasn't that he was out of work or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No. It was just beer as was the cause of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you ever remember feeling that your parents had a job to make ends meet when you were a child and how did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well I don't know as - as we were fixed that way. But - me dad were - worked in pit. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 He had quite a good job then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 And - there were 
one time he says to me mother he says, I've not much to draw this week. He says, I can't pay me draw, they were him as used to take his tubs out and fetch his empties in you see, he used to fetch empties in and take full 'ens out. He said, I won't be able
 to pay me drawer his wage. He says, I - else I've worked for nothing and shall have to take some money from home for pay drawer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Why did he have such a short week that week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - he were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Was it because he'd been sick or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
No, it were just where he got his coal from - the coal face, it were - it were hard do you see. And he couldn't get as much coal so he couldn't fill as many tubs for his wage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 But he'd still got to pay the drawer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 But he'd still his drawer for - he had to pay his drawer's wage if he got nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you ever remember your father being out of work or never having any pay at all through being sick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 He never were out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You never had to have help from anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 And if anyb
ody were grumbling about - having a bad place - they used to say, I'll send old Bill in, that were me dad. Says, he - he'll work it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No matter how bad it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Aye. He'd work it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you remember why you moved houses, when you moved from one house to another do you remember why it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well we lived in a house - we lived in that house of ours forty-years. We didn't move about a lot. But - this here -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you remember your school days, how young you were when you started and what age you finished?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
I know - I know there used to be a - they used to like a little trap as come for us. It were like a little gig you know. And take us t' school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Was it a long way away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No, it wasn't a long way away but - we - we used to enjo
y riding. And - he used to come, he says, come on, get out to your school. So he used to get in it take us school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Who was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - he - he were - he were really a farmer. You see. And he used to go t' market. And there were certain days he 
- he'd ride us t'school when he were going t'market you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How old were you when you started school, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Ah about four - I were about four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What age did you finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Leaving age was thirteen then. Yes. But - you could go half time at twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you go half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
I didn't go half time, no, but there were some as when they got twelve year old they'd go half time and they used to have a - an attendance book and they had to take that to the work for when they were
 working, whether it was morning or afternoon - vice versa, they had to take it to school after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 To show that they'd attended either work or school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Yes. And that's - that's where - how they got they're half time work over. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What time did you start in the morning do you remember and what time you finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh it used to be eight o'clock we used to finish at four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You started at eight - that was early wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 But you say you came home to dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh we used come home for dinner and - back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Well - I - I liked - I liked in every class only - I only got in fourth - standard fourth - four that's all. And we had examination for go up into fifth and I never liked decimals and fractions. That's reason I fall back into fourth standard again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What kind of a school was it - was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh it - Church of England school. It was a Daisy Hill school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Was it boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - the different sections you know. The different sections, different doors for you go in and all. One for girls and t}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 other for boys. And it used to be - over top you know, boys and girls you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well I liked school but I - I didn't like all teachers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Because they used give us stick for nothing. A thing or nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you remember being punished and what it was for - did you ever get the stick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I got it for talking and showing - showing me next - me next lad how do his sums.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You got the stick for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I got stick for it. And when school teacher went out - I goes and gets the stick and I breaks it over me knee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What happened when she found out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 When - when her come back - nobody would tell h
er who'd broke this stick you know. No, nobody'd say who broke it. Anyway she got know some way or other and she fetched me out and I had to stand at back of blackboard all afternoon for it. But morning after she fetched another stick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you remember
 what the teachers taught you was important in life - manners or tidiness or being punctual or ways of speaking, do you remember what they said was important to learn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well we were never - we were never punctual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you get into trouble for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - she used put mark against our attendance do you see. How late you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What did she teach you was important though - tidiness or ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh yes, she wanted you tidy. Oh she wanted tidy. If you weren't tidy she'd send you 
home and - but you had to come back again, you know, you're not to stay at home. If you - if you'd a black face or anything like that - she wouldn't bother washing you, she'd tell you go in cloakroom and have a wash or else go home and come back again. Bu
t if you didn't come back again you send one of scholars for you then you used get stick for not coming back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Were your parents interested in what you did at school and did your mum ever go to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Just for - they just went to one of teachers - for giving me stick you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Well nothing did come of it you know. Her says, well, her says, if I don't give him stick, her says, I shall have to send him to headmaster and he gets strap there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 He used to give the strap did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Aye. She used a stick but if he - if her sent you t' headmaster - he used to lay you across desk with a strap. Smack your bottom with a strap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Were all the children from the same kinds of home as yourself in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh - oh y
es. Yes. Yes. There were all - they were all one class you see the - them as could go to these high schools you know, they had to pass a certain examination. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you ever remember hour teachers treating one child differently from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No, I don't as there was anything like that. I don't as there's anything like that. Not treating one any different to another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You never saw a child left out of anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well on field when they used to have the walking day you know. The - th
ey used to - they used to give you bun and coffee. Aye. But you had take your own cup tied in handkerchief you see. And there were - there were one little lad broke his cup - so he couldn't have any coffee, he could have his -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 So he was left out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 He were like being left out. Because - he broke his cup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you ever remember any gangs in-your school in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Gangs? Oh they - oh they used to - they used to get into gangs to play football at school yard you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 But that was all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
And - they used to play what they called tug-o'-war. That were a long rope you know and they had to pull at either end. Them as had the strongest pull you know, they pulled these others over you see, they called that tug-o'-war, used to play at that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 That was the only thing they had gangs for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 And - and girls used to play with these 'ere }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 \endash  shu}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 ttle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 cocks you know, with feathers round you know and a litt}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 le bit of a net thing for knock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 ing it up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you ever go to night school after you left Daisy Hill school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No, I'd had enough. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You wouldn't have stayed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 longer if you could have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you think you got any benefit out of going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - sometimes I did and sometimes I didn't. Because - the benefit as you got - were being made to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How did you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 That was the biggest benefit - and the biggest pull back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Tell me how you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - you were forced to go to school. And you - you didn't like going and when yo
u - when you got there you wasn't interested in what she was teaching you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
You were more interested in - in playing at something and drawing and something you see. And then her come round you know and - and see what you done you know - co
me out. Back of blackboard you had to go for about half an hour. Then fetch you back again to your seat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 You don't think it did you any good at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh yes, yes, it - it did do good in one sense. You - you're - you learned - you learned how to r
ead, you learned how to write and you - you learned how to behave yourself. But you didn't always do it. But you did learn - it were teach you - they teached it to you - to you. And - the schoolmaster used to get us all lined up and he used to talk to us 
on that. Do unto others as you would like to be done to yourself. That's what schoolmaster used to tell us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you have a part time job while you were at school at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
It was at Greenvale Print - Works at Daisy Hill, when I was thirteen. And - it were bleach - it were bleaching and dying. The same place is running now but I think it's an engineering firm as has got it now. And it's Charlie Spittal works and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well I - I got the job where - being recommended with somebody else do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you remember what pay you got and what hours you worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 And - well we used to finish at half past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What time did you start in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 We - well - six o'clock were our time of starting then, it were early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you work Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Not Sundays. We worked Saturdays. Saturdays 'til dinner time - 'til twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you remember what wage you got and what you thought about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
We'd only seven and sixpence a week, that's all. And we get a - a rise to eight shilling. And it's still at that eight shilling all time as I were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How old were you when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I wasn't
 there long because I was in a room and they called it the sky - sky room. All the - it was calico printing and it used be a sky blue this 'ere cloth as come through. And - you had to be at back side keeping all creases out while they went over a drum. Wh
e
n they went over this drum it dried 'em and it went over - it went along some rollers and then it went on a - a rail as used to work like that you know and it plated it all down. Laid it all down do you see. And - and when it is getting so high - all thes
e
 here - all this - all this calico was - calico was stitched do you see with - with string and when it was getting so high they'd pull this end out and they'd unstitch it and take it away and put another - leg underneath for catch the next lot and that us
ed go into a - into room for printing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What did you feel about the wages you got - did you think it was a fair wage for what you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh - oh it - it was a fair wage at that time for - what it was for living do you see, for - you could -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you give it to your mother or did you keep it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Oh I had to give it to me mam, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What did she use it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I - I gave it to me mam and her used to - now, you'll have wait 'til your dad comes home. I says, what for? Says, he'l
l decide what spending money you have to have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How did you lie the people you worked with and how did the boss treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - they - they had to treat you all right. If - if they didn't do you wouldn't do your work right. But this cloth - ope
ning this cloth up - out - it used make all your finger ends sore. Were kind of indigo blue was they put in do you see and it used make your fingers sore. And we used get - fingers off gloves - aye, we used to wear them just the same. But that's reason I 
left - because all me fingers were sore.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Stothers was your next job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Tell me all about it - about your wage and the hours and what you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I told you about working at - Stothers didn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Not on the tape you didn't. What did you do when you mixed cough mixture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Well - I left there and - I went to Stothers from there from t' bleach works and first as I went I was put on washing bottle. This 'ere bottles as they take to shop with - Indi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 
an Brandy in and one thing and a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 not
her. So - when I'd been in - on that a bit - I got moved into warehouse. Making parcels up for - used to get bills you know and you had to make these parcels up do you see with all this stuff and - weep invoice up and shove it in you know and par - parcel
 
it up with name and address on that were ready for delivering. If they were bottles you just wrap bottle up and tied a - a tag round wit' - wit' name on do you see. Then used to be delivered wit' van when they went round you see. So - one time - fellow - 
c
hemist says - I'm asking manager for you t' come in dispensing. I says, all right, I'll come in. He says, he want you t' help Jim Whittle. Jim Whittle. I says, what's - who's Jim Whittle? Why he says, he finished stuff off and I put me own proportions in 
-
 chemist used to put main proportions in and he used finish it off and I had help him, I had to go and stir all this up. Finishing it off ready for it being bottled you know. Well with that I got to know these recipes you know and all stuff as we were mix
ing, do you see. So that's where I got making a bit of cough mixture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 And you used to do it at home did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I used to do that at home but I knew what I was getting because I could go to chemist and get it but you can't now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 At home did you sell it to people or did you just make it for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
No, I - I only made it for meself for - for relatives that's all. I never sold it. But - at Stothers we used get a tremendous lot you know. And I knew all as were going in - I knew - I had the r
ecipe, in fact I booked it down, I had a book for putting bits down as I wanted you see. And - when I left there - I went to - Wigglesworth at Westhoughton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What were you d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 ing there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 That - that's - that's like a chemist but - they make these '
ere childrens food - Mawsley food - Mawsley food. I daresay you've heard about Mawsley food haven't you. Well that's made by Wigglesworth of Westhoughton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 But I wasn't in that. I was helping tablet maker. They used to make tablets - pine tree lozenges, bromton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 lozenges. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 Sac}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
carin tablets. Anything in tablet form. So - anyway up - I used to help this tablet maker and mixing these stuff you know but it used to be all put in drums and they used go to for engineer and t' enginee
r used press 'em in machines. Tablet machines you know. Then they were all dropped into a drum after he'd pressed 'em and they went in the works, bottled up or packeted up or anything like that ready for sale do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Do you remember what wage you got at Stothers? And what hours you worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
Not much wage and I don't know - I've - we'd not much wage. You - you got more money as you rise - as you got lifted up into different departments do you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 How did the boss treat you at Stothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well they - he weros a sneak sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Why - what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 
You'd be doing your work and he'd be peaping round corner - watching. See - see if everybody were - whether they were miking or whether they were doing their work or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 What's makming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Marmaking with one another. Thumping or - or boxing with one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Did you like the job or would you have preferred to do something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 I - I liked it until I were called up at war you know. I were called up at war and I had go - go then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5600746 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 This is Wiggl-sworth you're talking about now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4659335 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 Well - I was with this tablet maker and I helping him mix all these 'ere com}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8394249\charrsid15163457 odities into - pine tree lozenges, brompton lozenges - s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6710063\charrsid15163457 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
